As part of events marking the Francophonie Week, the French Institut will host a food fair open to the residents of the FCT, tomorrow. An annual event, the Francophonie Week celebrates French cultures and language spoken by over 300 million people in the five continents of the globe. The celebration which kicked off Monday has seen a rich texture of European films, African griot storytelling, poetry and music every day to thrill participants. The Food and Craft Fair will close down the week-long activities. Food enthusiasts and adventurers will have the opportunity to delight their taste buds with several French cuisines and desserts. Event opens 2pm, on Saturday. 